page.title: 19GYMNASTICS,COTEHILL
page.content: On Wednesdays I go to gymnastics.I go with Charlotte,Stephanie and Hazel.We go in Hazel's mams car.My mam and Charlotte's mam take turns at bringing us back.It starts at quarter to five until quarter to six.Our teacher is called Terry.We have gymnastics at High Hesket school.There are two lessons.We go to the first one.When I come back I am always hungry.I am usually last one to have my tea.When we get there we get changed.Then Terry marks the register.After that we do a warm up.Sometimes we get the box out. I have passed badges 4and3. We are going to start badge two.To pass badge two you have to do headsprings,high forward roll,backward roll passing through handstand,handstand in to a forward roll,and a handstand in to a crab.
